The <strong><code>HTMLOptionElement</code></strong> interface represents <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/option" title="The HTML &lt;option&gt; element is used to define an item contained in a &lt;select&gt;, an &lt;optgroup&gt;, or a &lt;datalist&gt; element. As such, &lt;option&gt; can represent menu items in popups and other lists of items in an HTML document."><code>&lt;option&gt;</code></a> elements and inherits all classes and methods of the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLElement" title="The HTMLElement interface represents any HTML element. Some elements directly implement this interface, others implement it via an interface that inherits it."><code>HTMLElement</code></a> interface.